<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-06-18T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-06-18T06:00:00-05:00" n="619" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d619">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">860P.00/344: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-06-18T14:00:00+03:00">June 18,
                                    1941—2 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received June 18—1:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1163. I have received a report that on the night of June 13 the Soviet
                            authorities began mass arrests in Latvia. The arrests appear to be
                            evenly distributed throughout the country. My informant was not in a
                            position to furnish any information concerning the other Baltic
                            States.</p>
                        <p>I have also been informed that peasant labor has been requisitioned to
                            speed the completion of a large airport located some 30 miles north of
                                Libau.<note n="67" xml:id="d619fn67">Liepāja, Libava.</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>